{
  "ops": [
    {
      "op": "rename",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "pkg",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "package import path; defaults to the envelope's pkg"
        },
        {
          "name": "sym",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "symbol: Name or Type.Member; defaults to the envelope's sym"
        },
        {
          "name": "to",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "new name"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "rename",
          "sym": "Double",
          "to": "Twice"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "proves post-splice resolution: every rewritten reference must resolve to the renamed object; reference capture rejects even when the compiler is satisfied"
    },
    {
      "op": "set_body",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "pkg",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "package import path; defaults to the envelope's pkg"
        },
        {
          "name": "sym",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "symbol: Name or Type.Member; defaults to the envelope's sym"
        },
        {
          "name": "body",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "new body as statements, no surrounding braces"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "set_body",
          "sym": "Double",
          "body": "return v + v"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "the coarse escape hatch: replaces the whole block between braces, validated by typecheck like every other op"
    },
    {
      "op": "add_param",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "pkg",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "package import path; defaults to the envelope's pkg"
        },
        {
          "name": "sym",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "symbol: Name or Type.Member; defaults to the envelope's sym"
        },
        {
          "name": "name",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "new parameter name"
        },
        {
          "name": "type",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "new parameter type, e.g. context.Context"
        },
        {
          "name": "default",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "argument expression for existing call sites; required whenever the function already has callers"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "add_param",
          "pkg": "demo/sig",
          "sym": "Scale",
          "name": "offset",
          "type": "int",
          "default": "0"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "callers updated with default; a top-level local `name := \u003cdefault\u003e` in the body is superseded and deleted (parameters share the body scope), any other same-named body declaration is rejected with its position; references to the function as a value (assigned, passed, satisfying an interface) cannot be repaired and are rejected with their positions"
    },
    {
      "op": "upsert_decl",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "pkg",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "package import path; defaults to the envelope's pkg"
        },
        {
          "name": "text",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "complete declaration source, including doc comment if any; the symbol name is parsed from it"
        },
        {
          "name": "imports",
          "type": "[]{path,name}",
          "required": false,
          "description": "imports the declaration needs that goimports cannot infer: an aliased import or an ambiguous package name; name is the alias, empty for the default"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "upsert_decl",
          "pkg": "demo/lib",
          "text": "// Double doubles v.\nfunc Double(v int) int {\n\treturn v + v\n}"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "add or replace a whole top-level declaration; goimports runs in the loop. Replacement finds declarations in _test.go files too, and replaces single members inside grouped const/var/type blocks in place (send the standalone form; iota groups and members a following bare spec inherits from reject with the blocker named). New declarations append to an existing package file (test funcs to a _test.go file, so they actually run) and may reference symbols other ops in the same patch introduce; a package with no such file gets agent.go / agent_test.go created on demand — including a brand-new package mid-patch, so one atomic patch can create a package and move declarations into it"
    },
    {
      "op": "delete_decl",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "pkg",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "package import path; defaults to the envelope's pkg"
        },
        {
          "name": "sym",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "symbol: Name or Type.Member; defaults to the envelope's sym"
        },
        {
          "name": "syms",
          "type": "[]string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "batch form: several symbols delete together, so intra-set references (a helper and the test that used it) do not block"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "delete_decl",
          "sym": "Unused"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "rejected while any non-declaring reference remains outside the declaration itself (a recursive self-call does not count), outside the batch, and outside spans earlier ops in the same patch rewrote; the diagnostics list where. A member of a grouped const/var/type block excises in place (iota and inherited-value members reject, position defines them); a method whose receiver type deletes in the same batch skips the reference guard, the end-of-list typecheck arbitrates"
    },
    {
      "op": "set_doc",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "pkg",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "package import path; defaults to the envelope's pkg"
        },
        {
          "name": "sym",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "symbol: Name or Type.Member; defaults to the envelope's sym"
        },
        {
          "name": "text",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "doc comment body; each line is rendered with a \"// \" prefix"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "set_doc",
          "sym": "Double",
          "text": "Double doubles v."
        }
      ],
      "notes": "doc comment only; replaces an existing one rather than appending, and does not affect the typecheck surface"
    },
    {
      "op": "add_field",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "pkg",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "package import path; defaults to the envelope's pkg"
        },
        {
          "name": "sym",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "the struct type's name; defaults to the envelope's sym"
        },
        {
          "name": "name",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "new field name"
        },
        {
          "name": "type",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "new field type"
        },
        {
          "name": "tag",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "struct tag, without backticks"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "add_field",
          "sym": "Store",
          "name": "Tag",
          "type": "string"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "appended to the struct's field list; rejected if the name already exists"
    },
    {
      "op": "remove_field",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "pkg",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "package import path; defaults to the envelope's pkg"
        },
        {
          "name": "sym",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "field: Type.Field; defaults to the envelope's sym"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "remove_field",
          "sym": "Config.Legacy"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "rejected while referenced. v1 ceiling: a field sharing a multi-name declaration (\"a, b int\") or an embedded field is not supported"
    },
    {
      "op": "move_decl",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "pkg",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "source package import path; defaults to the envelope's pkg"
        },
        {
          "name": "sym",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "top-level declaration name; defaults to the envelope's sym"
        },
        {
          "name": "syms",
          "type": "array",
          "required": false,
          "description": "several declarations moving as one set (type + constructor + tests); intra-set references are legal; mutually exclusive with sym"
        },
        {
          "name": "to_pkg",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "target package import path (must exist by the time this op runs; an earlier upsert_decl in the same patch can create it)"
        },
        {
          "name": "create_pkg",
          "type": "boolean",
          "required": false,
          "description": "create a missing module-local target package as part of this patch; without it a missing target rejects (typo safety) and offers this flag as a repair"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "move_decl",
          "pkg": "demo/sig",
          "sym": "Fetch",
          "to_pkg": "demo/lib"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "relocates the whole declaration (doc comment included) and requalifies every reference, adding imports where needed; a type moves together with its whole method set, and one spec of a grouped const/var/type block extracts standalone. v1 ceilings: the declaration must be self-contained (no uses of its old package's other top-level symbols) and grouped specs may not lean on iota or an inherited value; each rejects with the blocking names"
    },
    {
      "op": "set_signature",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "pkg",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "package import path; defaults to the envelope's pkg"
        },
        {
          "name": "sym",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "symbol: Name or Type.Member; defaults to the envelope's sym"
        },
        {
          "name": "signature",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "the complete new signature as Go text: \"(params) results\""
        },
        {
          "name": "defaults",
          "type": "object",
          "required": false,
          "description": "argument expression per NEW parameter name, spliced into every existing call site; required for any new parameter when call sites exist"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "set_signature",
          "pkg": "demo/sig",
          "sym": "Fetch",
          "signature": "(ctx context.Context, a int, b string, rest ...int) int",
          "defaults": {
            "ctx": "context.Background()"
          }
        }
      ],
      "notes": "full parameter/result rewrite: parameters are matched to the old signature by name — carried ones keep each call site's argument (reordering reorders them), dropped ones drop it, new ones take their default; underscore params pair positionally when their type matches, so widening func(ctx context.Context, _ DecryptFn) keeps the _ argument; a spread call site f(args...) survives insertions before the variadic. Value uses of the function and the body itself are not rewritten: repair them with sibling ops in the same patch or the end-of-list typecheck rejects with the site positions"
    },
    {
      "op": "delete_file",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "path",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "file path relative to the module root (or absolute)"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "upsert_decl",
          "pkg": "demo/scratch",
          "text": "func Tmp() int {\n\treturn 0\n}"
        },
        {
          "op": "delete_file",
          "path": "scratch/agent.go"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "removes one file; rejected while any package-level symbol it declares is referenced from outside it (the rejection lists the reference positions). Deleting a package's last file removes the package"
    },
    {
      "op": "move_file",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "from",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "current file path relative to the module root (or absolute)"
        },
        {
          "name": "to",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "new file path; a different directory must hold an already-loaded package"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "move_file",
          "from": "lib/lib.go",
          "to": "lib/core.go"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "same-directory moves are pure renames; a cross-package move rewrites the package clause to the target package and drops a now-self import, and is rejected while the file declares symbols referenced from outside it (their qualifiers would all be wrong — use move_decl per declaration instead)"
    },
    {
      "op": "add_dependency",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "module",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "module path, e.g. golang.org/x/sync"
        },
        {
          "name": "version",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "module version; defaults to latest"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "add_dependency",
          "module": "golang.org/x/sync",
          "version": "v0.10.0"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "runs go get module@version against the workspace module; go.mod and go.sum restore byte-for-byte on any later rejection in the same patch. Needs the module in the local cache or network access"
    },
    {
      "op": "remove_dependency",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "module",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "module path to drop"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "remove_dependency",
          "module": "golang.org/x/sync"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "runs go get module@none; rejected while any workspace file still imports the module (the rejection lists the import positions)"
    },
    {
      "op": "mod_tidy",
      "args": [],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "mod_tidy"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "runs go mod tidy with the same go.mod/go.sum restore-and-validate wrapper as the other module ops"
    },
    {
      "op": "add_assign",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "at",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "handle (or $N) to place the statement relative to"
        },
        {
          "name": "where",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "before | after | first | last (first/last need a block-owning handle)"
        },
        {
          "name": "lhs",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "assignment target identifier"
        },
        {
          "name": "rhs",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "right-hand-side expression, parsed and typechecked in scope"
        },
        {
          "name": "define",
          "type": "bool",
          "required": false,
          "description": "use := instead of ="
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "add_assign",
          "at": "n2",
          "where": "after",
          "lhs": "_",
          "rhs": "h(3)",
          "define": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "op": "add_call",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "at",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "handle (or $N) to place the statement relative to"
        },
        {
          "name": "where",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "before | after | first | last"
        },
        {
          "name": "expr",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "a call expression or channel receive (\u003c-ch); assignments belong to add_assign"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "add_call",
          "at": "n2",
          "where": "after",
          "expr": "fmt.Println(h(1))"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "op": "add_return",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "at",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "handle (or $N) to place the statement relative to"
        },
        {
          "name": "where",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "before | after | first | last"
        },
        {
          "name": "exprs",
          "type": "[]string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "result expressions, in order; omit for a bare \"return\""
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "add_return",
          "at": "n2",
          "where": "after",
          "exprs": [
            "h(2)"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": "arity and result types are checked against the enclosing signature at end-of-list typecheck, not here"
    },
    {
      "op": "add_defer",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "at",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "handle (or $N) to place the statement relative to"
        },
        {
          "name": "where",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "before | after | first | last"
        },
        {
          "name": "expr",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "a call expression"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "add_defer",
          "at": "n1",
          "where": "after",
          "expr": "fmt.Println(\"done\")"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "op": "add_go",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "at",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "handle (or $N) to place the statement relative to"
        },
        {
          "name": "where",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "before | after | first | last"
        },
        {
          "name": "expr",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "a call expression"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "add_go",
          "at": "n2",
          "where": "after",
          "expr": "h(1)"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "op": "delete_node",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "at",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "handle of the statement or case clause to remove"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "add_return",
          "at": "n3",
          "where": "after",
          "exprs": [
            "h(9)"
          ]
        },
        {
          "op": "delete_node",
          "at": "n3"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "a block-owning statement with children, or an if with an else, is rejected rather than silently discarding content — delete children first"
    },
    {
      "op": "add_if",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "at",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "handle (or $N) to place the statement relative to"
        },
        {
          "name": "where",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "before | after | first | last"
        },
        {
          "name": "cond",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "condition expression"
        },
        {
          "name": "else",
          "type": "bool",
          "required": false,
          "description": "also create an empty else block"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "add_if",
          "at": "n2",
          "where": "after",
          "cond": "h != nil",
          "else": false
        }
      ],
      "notes": "returns the new then-block's own handle via $N; there is no v1 handle for a requested else block (view again to reach it)"
    },
    {
      "op": "add_for",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "at",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "handle (or $N) to place the statement relative to"
        },
        {
          "name": "where",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "before | after | first | last"
        },
        {
          "name": "cond",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "condition expression; mutually exclusive with range"
        },
        {
          "name": "range",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "a full range clause, e.g. \"k, v := range coll\"; mutually exclusive with cond"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "add_for",
          "at": "n2",
          "where": "after",
          "cond": "h(0) \u003e 0"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "empty body, returns its handle via $N. v1 ceiling: no init/post clauses — use upsert_decl/set_body for a classic three-clause loop"
    },
    {
      "op": "add_switch",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "at",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "handle (or $N) to place the statement relative to"
        },
        {
          "name": "where",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "before | after | first | last"
        },
        {
          "name": "tag",
          "type": "string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "switch tag expression; omit for a tagless switch"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "add_switch",
          "at": "n2",
          "where": "after",
          "tag": "h(1)"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "empty body; extend with add_case"
    },
    {
      "op": "add_case",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "at",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "handle (or $N) of the switch statement to extend"
        },
        {
          "name": "exprs",
          "type": "[]string",
          "required": false,
          "description": "case expressions; mutually exclusive with default"
        },
        {
          "name": "default",
          "type": "bool",
          "required": false,
          "description": "make this the default clause; mutually exclusive with exprs"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "add_switch",
          "at": "n2",
          "where": "after",
          "tag": "h(1)"
        },
        {
          "op": "add_case",
          "at": "$1",
          "exprs": [
            "1",
            "2"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": "always appends as the last clause (v1 has no argument for placing a case among existing ones); returns the new case's body handle via $N"
    },
    {
      "op": "set_cond",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "at",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "handle (or $N) of the if/for/case to retarget"
        },
        {
          "name": "expr",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "replacement condition"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "add_if",
          "at": "n2",
          "where": "after",
          "cond": "h == nil"
        },
        {
          "op": "set_cond",
          "at": "$1",
          "expr": "h != nil"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "a case clause's whole expression list is replaced as one; v1 has no per-element case-expr addressing"
    },
    {
      "op": "replace_expr",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "at",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "handle (or $N) of the target node"
        },
        {
          "name": "expr",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "replacement expression"
        }
      ],
      "example": [
        {
          "op": "add_call",
          "at": "n2",
          "where": "after",
          "expr": "h(1)"
        },
        {
          "op": "replace_expr",
          "at": "$1",
          "expr": "h(2)"
        }
      ],
      "notes": "v1 ceiling: an if/for/case condition or a whole expression statement only; per-argument sub-expression handles are future work"
    },
    {
      "op": "wrap_stmts",
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "from",
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "handle (or $N) of the first statement to enclose"
        },
        {
          "name": "to",
